de.cocolab.reuse
Interface Comparable

All Known Implementing Classes:
Position
public interface Comparable

This interface specifies an ordering on the objects of each class that implements it. It is used instead of java.lang.Comparable from JDK 1.2 so that Cocktail is usable on earlier Java platforms.

Arrays of objects that implement this interface can be sorted by sort in class Sort.

compareTo

public int compareTo(java.lang.Object other)
Compare this object with the specified object.

Parameters:
other - The Object to be compared.
Returns:
a negative integer if this < other, positive if this > other, or zero if they are equal.
Throws:
ClassCastException - if the specified object's type prevents it from being compared to this Object.
